HEADWORD: Romish
<hw>Rom"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Belonging or relating
to Rome, or to the Roman Catholic Church; -- frequently used in a
disparaging sense; <as>as, the <ex>Romish</ex> church; the
<ex>Romish</ex> religion, ritual, or ceremonies.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

